<!-- What Is a Qi2 Desktop Wireless Charger -->
<section class="sec bg-white relative py-16">
 <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
 <h2 class="section-title text-center">What Is a Qi2 Desktop Wireless Charger?</h2>
 <p class="text-center text-slate-500 text-sm max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-8">A Qi2 desktop wireless charger is a <strong>single-device or multi-device charging accessory</strong> designed for desks, nightstands, and office workspaces. Available in two form factors — <strong>flat pad</strong> (phone lies horizontal) and <strong>vertical stand</strong> (phone held upright for Face ID and video calls) — modern Qi2 desktop chargers use the MPP (Magnetic Power Profile) standard with N52H neodymium magnets for perfect snap alignment and 15W-25W fast charging. For B2B buyers, desktop wireless chargers represent the <strong>highest-volume segment in the category</strong> — single-device pads and stands account for 55-60% of all wireless charger unit shipments globally, making them essential for brands, Amazon sellers, corporate gift programs, and retailer house brands.</p>

 <blockquote class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-12 bg-brandOrange/5 border-l-4 border-brandOrange rounded-r-xl px-6 py-5 text-sm text-slate-700 italic leading-relaxed">
  <p>"The global desktop wireless charging stand market was valued at $1.45-2.41 billion in 2024 and is projected to reach $5.72-7.54 billion by 2033, growing at a 16.5-17.2% CAGR (DataIntelo/MarketIntelo). Global single-PAD wireless charger sales reached approximately 140 million units in 2025 at an ASP of $21.20 (QYResearch). Critically, the iPhone-specific wireless charger segment shows a supply-demand ratio of 19.8 — severe undersupply — with an 89.2% blue ocean opportunity score on Alibaba.com (2026). Qi2.2 25W certification, ultra-slim form factors, and patented designs are the three key differentiators for brands entering this high-volume market."</p>
